Dedicado a la mujer
 
Jardín de hermosura
Que a tu paso florecen las razones del amor;
Dichoso el viento que tu cuerpo acacia sin cesar,
Bendita la tierra que tus pies sostiene
Y guarda el recuerdo de tus pasos.
Juegas con el tiempo,
Rompes sus reglas de linealidad invariable
Y de él te haces dueña.
 
Transmite alegría tu sonrisa
Y tu palabra es consuelo;
Abrigo hay en tus brazos
En tu mirada consentimiento;
De ti nace la ternura,
De tus besos la pasión,
Tus caricias le dan sosiego
Hasta al león más feroz.
 
Miles de cosas puede un hombre lograr
Pero es tu cariño que desea encontrar.
De grandes triunfos puede uno jactarse
Pero insignificantes son para contigo compararse.
 
Te hace perfecta tu imperfecta creación;
En ti se resume todo,
La sutileza, la vida, el mundo;
Los deseos y placeres son incompletos sin ti;
Eres el sentido de un camino sin rumbo,
La luz que vence la oscuridad en la noche más tenebrosa
Espantando los temores de mis indecisiones.
 
Tanto podría decirse de ti
Pero carecen las palabras,
Habría que inventar muchas más
Y no serían suficientes
Para describir tu inmaculado ser.
 
La tierra, la naturaleza y la vida son bellas,
De eso no hay duda,
Pero es más que insistencia,
Es evidencia que la belleza es lo que es
Porque es mujer.

In this chapter of my life, I have been facing new challenges and presented with many opportunities for expansion and growth. I’ve been in uncomfortable positions and some more favorable ones. This has also been a time of personal reflection and adjustment; in which I realized the importance of knowing one’s true identity, both professionally and spiritually. 

That spiritual part — will help balance and connect all parts of your life. 

I invite you, whoever is reading this, to take some time today to meditate and speak to God (or the universe, or the sun, or your pillow) about your concerns, your goals, your purpose and the challenges you’re facing. I invite you to take a moment and think about the size of your city, your state, your country, and then the size of our planet. Then, the size of our galaxy, and then the universe. In comparison to all these things, us humans are very so very small; and our problems are smaller than us. 

Put things into perspective. 

#readthis

Here’s to goodbye, 2023. 

This year definitely broke me down and built me up in the most brutal way possible. Yes, I’m being honest. But I want to list a few things I did this year that will set the tone for the next: 

- I PRODUCED my ass off. Yes, that one is important because this year was super unstable for the entire industry and still being able to find opportunities to grow and bring projects to life has been a blessing. 

- I learned to not take life so seriously. I’m super responsible and that also makes me an over thinker. I want everything to happen on time and in order, but this year taught me HARD to let go of the things I can’t control. 

- I started writing my first novel at the beginning of this year, and honestly I don’t know how many years it’s going to take. 

- I shot a project back in the motherland 🇩🇴 it’s literally doing my favorite thing in my favorite place with my favorite people. 

- I made a lot of promises to myself and got a lot of clarity on knowing what I DONT want in my life. 

I take a lot of pride in the (did I say brutal yet?) growth I’ve had this year. But I learned to take life as it happens, so 2024 I have no expectations for you. Just pull up.
